<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17577] Greedy flag causing consumer health check to fail</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17577</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Polling consumer using greedy flag to immediately poll again for large size of messages available are causing consumer health checks to fail for a possibly &quot;long&quot; time. In an environment like a Kubernates cluster this could cause recurring pod restarts that might tighten the need to use greedy because of a growing size of messages needed to be polled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The variable firstPoolDone (btw rename to first&lt;b&gt;Poll&lt;/b&gt;Done) in ScheduledPollConsumer should also be set true if first greedy run has been finished.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
